# title = The Monkey and Her Two Babies
# sent_id = perry-218-s1
# text = Δύο τέκνων μητέρα τὸν πίθηκον εἶναι ἀκήκοα· ἀμφοτέροις οὖν κληρονομίαν χαρίζεσθαι, τῷ μὲν τὸ μῖσος, τῷ δὲ τὴν οἰκείαν ἀγάπην, δι' ἧς καὶ ἀποκτείνει τὸ πεφιλημένον, συχνῶν περιπτυσσομένη καὶ περιλείχουσα.
# parallel_id = lyceum-aesop-p218/s1
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = I have heard that a monkey was a mother of two children; she was therefore granting an inheritance to both — to the one hatred, to the other her own love, through which she also kills the beloved one, often embracing and licking it.
# literal_translation = Two of children mother the monkey to be I have heard; to both therefore an inheritance to grant, to the one hatred, to the other her own love, through which also she kills the beloved, often embracing and licking.
